# Cloudflare Pages Redirects file — edge-level 301s evaluated before
# the trailing-slash 308 layer, so a single rule per path catches the
# request directly (no double-hop).

# /security is a common UX convention (GitHub, Stripe, Cloudflare all
# expose it) but RFC 9116 standardizes the endpoint at
# /.well-known/security.txt. Forward both shapes to the canonical one
# so manual /security probes don't 404.
/security   /.well-known/security.txt  301
/security/  /.well-known/security.txt  301
